  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f13712cf8812799d34b7cdcbc686b9",
        "content": [
          "Identifiers and sorting\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "**RealCID and CID are the same identifier** — use either in joins or filters; choose one consistently within a query. For presenting results, either column is acceptable unless the user asks for a specific one.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Do not ORDER BY on identifiers — never sort by CID, RealCID, PositionID, or any raw ID column unless the user explicitly asks for ordering by that ID. Prefer ordering by business fields (name, date, amount, region) or leave order undefined when not specified.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Customer snapshot and time (customer_snapshot_v)\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Current status (today’s view of the customer: club, region, status, etc.): always filter main.etoro_kpi.customer_snapshot_v to Yesterday’s DateID — the completed daily snapshot for the prior calendar day. Do not use MAX(DateID), open-ended “latest row,” or an unspecified date for this pattern.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Historical analysis (attributes or joins for past periods): always filter customer_snapshot_v with explicit DateID predicates — e.g. DateID = …, DateID BETWEEN … AND …, or DateID IN (…) matching the user’s timeframe. Do not use WHERE DateID = (SELECT MAX(DateID) FROM …) or similar “latest available” logic when the user asked for a historical range or specific dates.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "When joining customer_snapshot_v to ddr_aum_v, ddr_mimo_v, or ddr_revenue_v, match RealCID and DateID on both sides so facts and dimensions align to the same calendar day.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Other rules\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "If no timeframe is mentioned, ask for one before writing SQL.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "For current funded and DDR activity-style flags (IsFunded, IsActiveTrade, BalanceOnly, PortfolioOnly, IsChurn, IsWinback), use main.etoro_kpi.ddr_customer_current_flags joined on RealCID (partial coverage: current status only, not a daily snapshot with DateID). Combine with customer_snapshot_v (yesterday’s DateID) when the question also needs club, region, verification, or account status fields—those attributes are not guaranteed to describe the same calendar day as the flags. This companion view is the open SCD row only (ToDateID = 99991231); historical daily values for those flags require a different query on the underlying prep table.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "No instrument-level data in this Genie — only instrument type. Example: Crypto yes, BTC no. Stocks yes, Tesla no. Forex yes, USD/GBP no. If the user asks about a specific asset (instrument), say data is only available at asset type / instrument type level.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "All measures and fields whose names contain Count should use **SUM** as the aggregation.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "period-end (ddr_aum_v): when the timeframe is weekly / monthly / quarterly / yearly, filter with **IsLastDayWeek = 1**, **IsLastDayMonth = 1**, **IsLastDayQuarter = 1**, or **IsLastDayYear = 1** respectively (in addition to any DateID / snapshot rules above).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "Lifecycle milestones (registration, FTD, verification, first trade, club, funding): use **main.etoro_kpi.vg_customer_customer_first_dates** when the question is about first occurrence dates, not for “current customer status” — current attributes (club, region, verification, account status, etc.) still use **customer_snapshot_v** with Yesterday’s DateID. Current DDR funded / activity terminology flags use **main.etoro_kpi.ddr_customer_current_flags** joined on RealCID (see row above)."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "join_specs": [
      {
        "id": "01f1371669131b809f834208e14bebd2",
        "left": {
          "identifier": "main.etoro_kpi.customer_snapshot_v",
          "alias": "customer_snapshot_v"
        },
        "right": {
          "identifier": "main.etoro_kpi.ddr_revenue_v",
          "alias": "ddr_revenue_v"
        },
        "sql": [
          "customer_snapshot_v.`RealCID` = ddr_revenue_v.`RealCID` AND customer_snapshot_v.`DateID` = ddr_revenue_v.`DateID`",
          "--rt=FROM_RELATIONSHIP_TYPE_ONE_TO_MANY--"
        ],
        "instruction": [
          "Left Join on RealCID+DateID. Revenue rows only exist when activity occurred."
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "01f137168c3c1a4cb9de5c5a6a59eede",
        "left": {
          "identifier": "main.etoro_kpi.customer_snapshot_v",
          "alias": "customer_snapshot_v"
        },
        "right": {
          "identifier": "main.etoro_kpi.ddr_mimo_v",
